<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="371" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Loubet</persName> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-11"><hi rend="italic">May 11,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I thank Your Excellency for the expression of profound sympathy you have
                            sent me in the name of the American people on the occasion of the awful
                            catastrophe in Martinique. The French people will certainly join me in
                            thanks to the American people.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Emile Loubet.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>